{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"af16106f-57a5-4c24-8c44-c1f606f655b3","content":"On macOS, when a process crashes the system automatically generates a **crash report**. You can find it in:\n\n1. **`~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`** — user-level crash reports\n2. **`/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/`** — system-level crash reports\n\nLook for a `.ips` or `.crash` file matching your process name and timestamp.\n\nYou can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse them with a GUI.\n\n**For a core dump** (if you need one for `lldb`):\n\n```bash\n# Enable core dumps\nulimit -c unlimited\n# Reproduce the crash — core file appears in /cores/\nls /cores/\n```\n\nThen attach with:\n```bash\nlldb --core /cores/core.<pid> ./YourApp\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0e1cfc14-f3a7-465f-919a-2db2d9079809","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS, without `createdump`. This is a general knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":256},"id":"a78e8d86-f418-4ff4-ac26-f15216be72c1","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:59:38.599Z","parentId":"e6246c44-81ab-4966-a110-e12aaf728a3d"}
